# Security (todo app)

- Never write, log, echo, or commit secrets, API keys, production credentials, or contents of `.env`, `config/master.key`, or `config/credentials/*.key`.
- Never use `eval`, `instance_eval`, or `class_eval` on user-controlled input (`params`, request body, headers).
- Never call `html_safe` or `raw` on untrusted strings (user input, params, external API data).
- Use ActiveRecord / parameterized queries only; never interpolate user input into SQL strings.
- Do not disable CSRF protection, strong parameters, or mass-assignment guards.
- This app has no Devise; if auth is added later, do not skip session or authentication callbacks without review.
- Do not expose stack traces or internal paths in production responses.
- Filter sensitive keys in logs (`config/initializers/filter_parameter_logging.rb` patterns).
